London m. George Cole
In answer toyd of 5h past did not exspect that itt should bave bee
si long that the rest of JB acctt is impayd, nothwithstanding my endeavors
to gett ill in yett I sope ven suddainly to remitt itt you, itt beeng romsed
mee ths monts. as for colchester perpet. they ae butt vee little demande
sev, so that I am not incorridged to inorder any, bett in time I may finde
out some thing to keep ours correspondeney
London mr. W Scaven
C 17d.
In answer toyd of 22th past, am glad you rec the tykes sent you bope you
found them to content, as also a good markett for the same whe y
please to save any more give mee yd. onders & they shall be puneiually
observed. yd bill I have accepted & past to my acctt., as for the callier
att Brussels m. Sabbarton told mee that S. V. Jath pr un the valee
toot them to him self, I haveing poyd yd bill for acctt. & by ord of m
Sabbarton, in the meane while I s defist till next sale

van £101- inber, de welcke hope ul sal sijn gewoorden & behoorlijcq bet., de leste segoisel
wolle geepant. hebbende, bevinde geensins tot content. uyt te vallen, alsoo sij seer lackseert
